\alpha=\frac{2\pi p}h+ O_H\big(\lambda^\beta \big).$$ If $p>Ch>h/4$, the error term is analytic in $p$ and satisfies the estimate $$\label{est:error:alpha}
 \Big(O_H\big(\lambda^\beta\big)\Big)'_p=O_H\big(\lambda^\beta\big).$$*

</div>

